  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: gen-ai-opt-in (npm)",
  "details": "The postinstall hook runs postinstall.js which collects the installer's external IP address, geo-location (city, region, country, ISP, organization), hostname, and username. This data is encoded into a DNS subdomain and exfiltrated via a DNS lookup to p1r2d74iwjk057raam6myf7e258wzkt8i[.]oastify[.]com, an attacker-controlled OAST callback host. The package also fetches geo-location data from ip-api[.]com/json/ during the exfiltration process. Both packages (gen-ai-opt-in and ai-gen-ai-opt-in) contain identical payloads with the same C2 domain.",
